      "put": {
        "tags": [
          "Url management - Writers"
        ],
        "summary": "Create or update a service in an environment",
        "description": "\nThis endpoint allows for the creation or updating of a service in an environment.\n            If the service with the specified identifier exists, it will be replaced with the provided details.\n            If it does not exist, a new service will be created.\n            The endpoint requires authentication and is accessible to roles Writer or Administrator.\n            It provides detailed error responses for unauthorized, forbidden and not found scenarios.\n\nSample request\n```\nPUT /api/v1/environments/{environmentId}/services/{serviceId}\n{\n  \"service1\": {\n    \"url\" : \"https://service1.sample.azure.com\",\n    \"enabled\" : \"true\"\n  }\n}\n            \n```",
